<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/261a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-08T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 8,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Is Leguia planning to have new congressional elections and if
                                    so when?</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>Is he planning new presidential election?</item>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>Have you tangible evidence in your possession that statements
                                    made by Leguia party which have appeared in the press are true,
                                    to the effect that Pardo attempted to use fraud in decision of
                                    presidential election contest?</item>
                            </list>
                            <p>Rush reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>